  "original_title": "No petrol delivery for CPC until July 22",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "No petrol delivery for CPC until July 22",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The Ceylon Petroleum Corporation (CPC) will not receive shipments of petrol until July 22, even if the funds are available with the CPC, the Chief of Staff of the Prime Minister, Sagala Ratnayake said.",
        "Addressing the media, he said only 1,000 MT of diesel, 30,000 MT of furnace oil and 800 MT of jet fuel are available at the CPC storage facility.",
        "Meanwhile, he said\u00a0 38,000 MT of diesel would be due between July 11 and 15.",
        "Therefore, the existing stock of diesel will only be available for essential services until the new\u00a0 consignment reaches the country.",
        "There will be no issue with domestic gas supply, as LITRO Gas Lanka Ltd., will procure 100,000 MT of gas for the next four months and\u00a0 another 33,000 MT of gas will arrive in the country on July 6, 10, 16, 19, 21 and 31. (Chaturanga Samarawickrama)"
      ],
